captions.text:
-Hi, it's Brooklyn from
Brooklyn and Bailey,

and today I'm
going to be showing

you guys two different
styles of Valentine nail.

And I don't know about you,
but I love wearing, like,

themed nail polish
for the holiday.
So I'm super excited.

I think you guys will
totally love this one.

First, you're going to want to
take your CND of base coat nail

polish and apply it to
the naked nail-- naked,
what a weird word.
Anyways-- apply it to the nail.

And this just keeps your
nail polish on longer.

Next, you're going to want to
take your pink nail polish.

I'm using Pink Forever,
Sinful Colors Pink.

But, you know, you can
use whatever brand of pink
you want for Valentine's Day.

And you're just going to want
to apply to that same nail.

Next, you're going to want to
take your red nail art pen.

And I don't remember
for the life of me
where we bought these.

But we bought them, I
guess, since I have them.

But you're going to
want to draw a red X

kind of in the
middle of your nail.

Last but not least,
you're going to want

to take your mini pears, which
you can buy at Hobby Lobby,

and just place it to the right
next to your X-- and they do

have a sticky
bottom, so they will

stick to the nail-- creating the
perfect Valentine's XO design.

For my next tutorial, I'm going
to just take red nail polish--

Eye of China glaze-- but you
can use whatever, you know,

nail polish brand
you like in favor.

But just take it and apply the
red nail polish to your finger.

Next, you're just going to
want to take a heart hole

puncher, which you can find at
any, like, local craft store,

and punch a heart into your
tape-- just plain Scotch tape.

Then you're going to
want to take the tape

and place the heart in
the middle of your nail.

Now you're going to want to take
your white nail polish-- I'm

just using China
Glaze white-- and you

want to paint just a tiny,
thin layer over the heart hole.

Blow on it for a
second-- it doesn't

matter if it's completely
dry-- and then just
peel your tape off.

And don't worry if
it's not perfect,
because you can always fix it.

Thank you guys so
much for watching.

I hope you guys enjoyed
this nail tutorial
as much as I have.

Don't forget to
comment below on who

your crushing on
this Valentine's Day.

Be sure to follow us on
Twitter at BrookAndBailey.

And for an extra added bonus
to this video, the next time

you guys will see me in a video
at all, I have my braces off.

I Will not be a metal mouth
Six years of being this,
and it's all going to go away.

So be sure to watch
next time, because it'll

be kind of this, like, revealing
thing with me and my braces
off.
So we'll see you guys next week.
Bye!

-And the guest
whose water this is,

is the guy she
falls in love with.

He actually doesn't have
cancer, like, in the book.

Like almost halfway through
the book, he's in remission.

(MUSIC PLAYING) You
can do anything.
-Set.
OK.
Ready?

-And I don't know about you,
but I love wearing, like,

themed fingernail
polish for the holiday.
So I'm super excited.

I think you guys will
totally love this one.
